THE PILOT STATED THAT DURING THE GROUND ROLL PHASE OF LANDING AT RED 
LODGE, MT, HE LOST CONTROL OF THE AIRCRAFT WHICH ENTERED INTO A GROUND 
LOOP TO THE RIGHT. JUST PRIOR TO THE AIRCRAFT DEPARTING THE RIGHT SIDE OF THE 
RUNWAY, HE APPLIED MAXIMUM BRAKING, AND THE AIRCRAFT NOSED OVER INTO A SNOW 
BANK. 
